theorem Topology.interior_eq_empty_iff_closure_compl_eq_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) ↔
      closure (Aᶜ : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  classical
  -- Express `interior A` as the complement of `closure Aᶜ`.
  have h_int :
      interior (A : Set X) = (closure (Aᶜ : Set X))ᶜ := by
    simpa using
      (Topology.interior_compl_eq_compl_closure (X := X) (A := Aᶜ))
  -- Step 1: rewrite the left‐hand side via `h_int`.
  have h₁ :
      (interior (A : Set X) = (∅ : Set X)) ↔
        (closure (Aᶜ : Set X))ᶜ = (∅ : Set X) := by
    constructor
    · intro h; simpa [h_int] using h
    · intro h; simpa [h_int] using h
  -- Step 2: an empty complement is equivalent to the set being `univ`.
  have h₂ :
      (closure (Aᶜ : Set X))ᶜ = (∅ : Set X) ↔
        closure (Aᶜ : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    constructor
    · intro h_empty
      -- If the complement is empty, every point lies in the set.
      apply Set.eq_univ_of_forall
      intro x
      by_contra hx
      have : x ∈ (closure (Aᶜ : Set X))ᶜ := hx
      have : x ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
        simpa [h_empty] using this
      exact this.elim
    · intro h_univ
      -- The complement of `univ` is empty.
      simpa [h_univ, Set.compl_univ]
  -- Combine the two equivalences.
  exact h₁.trans h₂

theorem Topology.interior_closure_interior_closure_eq_of_P1 {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : Topology.P1 (X := X) A) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) := by
  -- First, upgrade `P1` from `A` to `closure A`.
  have h_closure : Topology.P1 (X := X) (closure A) :=
    Topology.P1_closure_of_P1 (X := X) (A := A) hA
  -- Apply the existing equality for sets satisfying `P1`.
  have h_eq :
      interior (closure (closure (A : Set X))) =
        interior (closure (interior (closure A))) :=
    Topology.interior_closure_eq_interior_closure_interior_of_P1
      (X := X) (A := closure A) h_closure
  -- Simplify the left‐hand side and reorient the equality.
  simpa [closure_closure] using h_eq.symm
